{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-resume-tsx","path":"/resume-en","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1>Personal Information</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Felix Chen</strong>/Male</li>\n<li>Master/Graduated at 2017/East China University of Science and Technology/Computer Science and Technology</li>\n<li>Blog: <a href=\"https://chennima.github.io/blog\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://chennima.github.io/blog</a></li>\n<li>Github: <a href=\"https://github.com/ChenNima\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/ChenNima</a></li>\n<li>LinkedIn: <a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/yifei-chen-990199110/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.linkedin.com/in/yifei-chen-990199110/</a></li>\n<li>E-mail: <a href=\"mailto:fennu637@sina.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">fennu637@sina.com</a><span class=\"d-none\"> / Phone：18918561263</span></li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Open Source Projects</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Chorus-AIDLC/chorus\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Chorus</a>: An Agent harness framework based on <a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/devops/ai-driven-development-life-cycle/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">AI-DLC</a> methodology, adopting Reversed Conversation mode (AI proposes, humans review), enabling AI Agents and humans to collaborate on product delivery from Idea to Proposal to Task\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Chorus-AIDLC/Chorus/tree/main/public/chorus-plugin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Claude Code Plugin</a>: Automatic Session management and context injection for Sub-Agents in Agent Teams (Swarm) scenarios via Hooks mechanism</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@chorus-aidlc/chorus-openclaw-plugin\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">OpenClaw Plugin</a>: SSE + MCP dual-channel architecture enabling AI Agents to autonomously detect tasks and drive product delivery 24/7</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Working Experience</h1>\n<h2>Amazon Web Services （ 2023.6 ~ Present ）</h2>\n<h3><strong>Solutions Builder</strong>/<small>AWS Solutions</small> （ 2023.6 ~ Present ）</h3>\n<p>Design and develop AWS-based industry solutions, focusing on healthcare and AI Agent domains</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Solution Development:\n<ul>\n<li>Developed MCS (Marketing &#x26; Commercial Set), an AI-powered knowledge management and training assistant for pharmaceutical sales teams based on <a href=\"https://strandsagents.com/latest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Strands Agents</a> and <code>Amazon Bedrock</code>. Built GraphRAG knowledge graph with <code>Amazon Neptune</code> + <code>OpenSearch Serverless</code>, supporting STAR case methodology, AI-driven sales strategy recommendation and simulation training</li>\n<li>Developed <a href=\"https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/ony8yF8s_gP7NAcLeU9r6w\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Medical Deep Insights</a>, a medical content generation assistant based on <a href=\"https://strandsagents.com/latest/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Strands Agents</a>. Supports rapid Agent and Tool generation via YAML configuration and AI coding assistant (Skill), integrates 15+ tools including PubMed/clinical trials/patent search, extends capabilities through MCP protocol, deployed on <code>Bedrock AgentCore</code></li>\n<li>Developed <a href=\"https://www.amazonaws.cn/en/solutions/industry/health/medical-insights-hub/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Medical Insights Hub</a>, an AWS-based medical content generation solution. GenAI-powered professional medical document translation with <code>OpenSearch Percolate</code> supporting million-level glossary matching; supports integration with external knowledge bases like PubMed for collaborative medical content generation, with Word plugin integration</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>SAP Labs China （ 2016.10 ~ 2023.6 ）</h2>\n<p>Architect, Web development (Frontend/backend), DevOps and data engineer.</p>\n<h3><strong>Architect</strong>/<small>SAP Concur</small> （ 2021.1 ~ 2023.6 ）</h3>\n<p>Design and develop SAP Concur eFapiao, a fapiao auto-recognition and validation system based on <code>NodeJS</code> and WeChat mini program</p>\n<ul>\n<li>DevOps:\n<ul>\n<li>Operating and deploying the project on AWS and <code>Kubernetes</code></li>\n<li>Service registration and discovery based on Concur customized <code>Istio</code>+<code>Envoy</code> service mesh</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Backend development:\n<ul>\n<li>Backend service based on <code>NodeJS</code> and <code>NestJS</code> framework</li>\n<li>Data backend based on AWS distributed database <code>DynamoDB</code></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Data engineering:\n<ul>\n<li>Collecting metrics generated by the running service and integrating with data pipeline via <code>AWS S3</code> and <code>AWS Kinesis</code> data stream</li>\n<li>Utilizing <code>AWS Glue Job</code> to implement data ETL jobs based on <code>Spark</code></li>\n<li>Utilizing <code>Grafana</code> and <code>AWS Athena</code> to query and visualize collected metrics data</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Machine learning:\n<ul>\n<li>Deploying OCR model based on <code>PaddleOCR</code> to mark unrecognized fields of fapiao images</li>\n<li>Training key information extraction model based on <code>SDMG-R</code> to extract key fields from fapiao images</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Senior DevOps</strong>/<small>SAP Jam Collaboration</small> （ 2019.3 ~ 2020.12 ）</h3>\n<p>SAP Jam Collaboration is a collaboration tool based on <code>Ruby on Rails</code>/<code>React</code>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Led the DevOps team to migrate the project from on-premise data centers to AWS <code>Kubernetes</code>, managing infrastructure and GitOps workflows with <code>Terraform</code>/<code>Helm</code>/<code>ArgoCD</code></li>\n<li>Introduced <code>Consul</code>+<code>HAproxy</code> for service discovery, deployed <code>Istio</code> Service Mesh for canary deployment and traffic monitoring</li>\n<li>Collaborated with international teams, supporting around-the-clock DevOps operations across multiple timezones</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Full Stack Developer</strong>/<small>SAP Jam Collaboration</small> （ 2017.10 ~ 2019.3 ）</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frontend: Built <code>BackboneJS</code> → <code>React</code>/<code>TypeScript</code> migration abstraction layer, enabling old and new code coexistence</li>\n<li>Backend: Developed <code>NodeJS</code>-based SSR service, <code>Golang</code>-based multi-storage file service (S3/Azure Blob/NAS)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>Frontend Developer</strong>/<small>SAP Jam Community</small> （ 2016.10 ~ 2017.10 ）</h3>\n<p>Frontend development for a social platform based on <code>EmberJS</code>/<code>Vue</code>/<code>Ruby on Rails</code></p>\n<h1>Certifications</h1>\n<p class=\"d-flex justify-content-between\">\n  <span style=\"width: 100px\"><span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 160px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/987925aef8bb6662bca2315a8ebf6054/69538/AWS-Certified-Machine-Learning-Engineer.png\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"AWS Certified Machine Learning Engineer\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/987925aef8bb6662bca2315a8ebf6054/69538/AWS-Certified-Machine-Learning-Engineer.png\" srcset=\"/static/987925aef8bb6662bca2315a8ebf6054/69538/AWS-Certified-Machine-Learning-Engineer.png 160w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 160px) 100vw, 160px\" style=\"widt